title: Hiroshige Ricefields and Torinomachi Festival Puzzle
description:
Japanese painter and printmaker, Utagawa Hiroshige (1797-1858), dominated the popular art of woodblock printing in the first half of the 19th century along with Hokusai. By subtly orchestrating colors and points of view, Hiroshige transformed everyday landscapes into intimate lyrical scenes, revering the passing moment.

Packaged in durable, compact boxes, our 500- Piece Puzzles feature full-color artwork, expertly printed with nontoxic inks on sturdy, puzzle greyboard.
  • Dimensions: Box size 7.8 x 6 x 2 in., Completed puzzle 14 x 19 in
  • 500 pieces
  • Recommended for ages 12 years and up
